42static const int CODEWORD_SKEW_SIZE = 2;
43static const int MAX_ERRORS = 3;
44static const int MAX_EC_CODEWORDS = 512;
45
46using ModuleBitCountType = std::array<int, CodewordDecoder::BARS_IN_MODULE>;
47
48static int AdjustCodewordStartColumn(const BitMatrix& image, int minColumn, int maxColumn, bool leftToRight, int codewordStartColumn, int imageRow)
49{
50 int correctedStartColumn = codewordStartColumn;
51 int increment = leftToRight ? -1 : 1;
52 // there should be no black pixels before the start column. If there are, then we need to start earlier.
53 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
54 while ((leftToRight ? correctedStartColumn >= minColumn : correctedStartColumn < maxColumn) &&
55 leftToRight == image.get(correctedStartColumn, imageRow)) {
56 if (std::abs(codewordStartColumn - correctedStartColumn) > CODEWORD_SKEW_SIZE) {
57 return codewordStartColumn;
58 }
59 correctedStartColumn += increment;
60 }
61 increment = -increment;
62 leftToRight = !leftToRight;
63 }
64 return correctedStartColumn;
65}
66
67static bool GetModuleBitCount(const BitMatrix& image, int minColumn, int maxColumn, bool leftToRight, int startColumn, int imageRow, ModuleBitCountType& moduleBitCount)
68{
69 int imageColumn = startColumn;
70 size_t moduleNumber = 0;
71 int increment = leftToRight ? 1 : -1;
72 bool previousPixelValue = leftToRight;
73 std::fill(moduleBitCount.begin(), moduleBitCount.end(), 0);
74 while ((leftToRight ? (imageColumn < maxColumn) : (imageColumn >= minColumn)) && moduleNumber < moduleBitCount.size()) {
75 if (image.get(imageColumn, imageRow) == previousPixelValue) {
76 moduleBitCount[moduleNumber] += 1;
77 imageColumn += increment;
78 }
79 else {
80 moduleNumber += 1;
81 previousPixelValue = !previousPixelValue;
82 }
83 }
84 return moduleNumber == moduleBitCount.size() || (imageColumn == (leftToRight ? maxColumn : minColumn) && moduleNumber == moduleBitCount.size() - 1);
85}
86
87static bool CheckCodewordSkew(int codewordSize, int minCodewordWidth, int maxCodewordWidth)
88{
89 return minCodewordWidth - CODEWORD_SKEW_SIZE <= codewordSize &&
90 codewordSize <= maxCodewordWidth + CODEWORD_SKEW_SIZE;
91}
92
93
94static ModuleBitCountType GetBitCountForCodeword(int codeword)
95{
96 ModuleBitCountType result;
97 result.fill(0);
98 int previousValue = 0;
99 int i = Size(result) - 1;
100 while (true) {
101 if ((codeword & 0x1) != previousValue) {
102 previousValue = codeword & 0x1;
103 i--;
104 if (i < 0) {
105 break;
106 }
107 }
108 result[i]++;
109 codeword >>= 1;
110 }
111 return result;
112}
113
114static int GetCodewordBucketNumber(const ModuleBitCountType& moduleBitCount)
115{
116 return (moduleBitCount[0] - moduleBitCount[2] + moduleBitCount[4] - moduleBitCount[6] + 9) % 9;
117}
118
119static int GetCodewordBucketNumber(int codeword)
120{
121 return GetCodewordBucketNumber(GetBitCountForCodeword(codeword));
122}
123
124static Nullable<Codeword> DetectCodeword(const BitMatrix& image, int minColumn, int maxColumn, bool leftToRight, int startColumn, int imageRow, int minCodewordWidth, int maxCodewordWidth)
125{
126 startColumn = AdjustCodewordStartColumn(image, minColumn, maxColumn, leftToRight, startColumn, imageRow);
127 // we usually know fairly exact now how long a codeword is. We should provide minimum and maximum expected length
128 // and try to adjust the read pixels, e.g. remove single pixel errors or try to cut off exceeding pixels.
129 // min and maxCodewordWidth should not be used as they are calculated for the whole barcode an can be inaccurate
130 // for the current position
131 ModuleBitCountType moduleBitCount;
132 if (!GetModuleBitCount(image, minColumn, maxColumn, leftToRight, startColumn, imageRow, moduleBitCount)) {
133 return nullptr;
134 }
135 int endColumn;
136 int codewordBitCount = std::accumulate(moduleBitCount.begin(), moduleBitCount.end(), 0);
137 if (leftToRight) {
138 endColumn = startColumn + codewordBitCount;
139 }
140 else {
141 std::reverse(moduleBitCount.begin(), moduleBitCount.end());
142 endColumn = startColumn;
143 startColumn = endColumn - codewordBitCount;
144 }
145 // TODO implement check for width and correction of black and white bars
146 // use start (and maybe stop pattern) to determine if blackbars are wider than white bars. If so, adjust.
147 // should probably done only for codewords with a lot more than 17 bits.
148 // The following fixes 10-1.png, which has wide black bars and small white bars
149 // for (int i = 0; i < moduleBitCount.length; i++) {
150 // if (i % 2 == 0) {
151 // moduleBitCount[i]--;
152 // } else {
153 // moduleBitCount[i]++;
154 // }
155 // }
156
157 // We could also use the width of surrounding codewords for more accurate results, but this seems
158 // sufficient for now
159 if (!CheckCodewordSkew(codewordBitCount, minCodewordWidth, maxCodewordWidth)) {
160 // We could try to use the startX and endX position of the codeword in the same column in the previous row,
161 // create the bit count from it and normalize it to 8. This would help with single pixel errors.
162 return nullptr;
163 }
164
165 int decodedValue = CodewordDecoder::GetDecodedValue(moduleBitCount);
166 if (decodedValue != -1) {
167 int codeword = CodewordDecoder::GetCodeword(decodedValue);
168 if (codeword != -1) {
169 return Codeword(startColumn, endColumn, GetCodewordBucketNumber(decodedValue), codeword);
170 }
171 }
172 return nullptr;
173}
174
175static DetectionResultColumn GetRowIndicatorColumn(const BitMatrix& image, const BoundingBox& boundingBox, const ResultPoint& startPoint, bool leftToRight, int minCodewordWidth, int maxCodewordWidth)
176{
177 DetectionResultColumn rowIndicatorColumn(boundingBox, leftToRight ? DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator::Left : DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator::Right);
178 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
179 int increment = i == 0 ? 1 : -1;
180 int startColumn = (int)startPoint.x();
181 for (int imageRow = (int)startPoint.y(); imageRow <= boundingBox.maxY() && imageRow >= boundingBox.minY(); imageRow += increment) {
182 auto codeword = DetectCodeword(image, 0, image.width(), leftToRight, startColumn, imageRow, minCodewordWidth, maxCodewordWidth);
183 if (codeword != nullptr) {
184 rowIndicatorColumn.setCodeword(imageRow, codeword);
185 if (leftToRight) {
186 startColumn = codeword.value().startX();
187 }
188 else {
189 startColumn = codeword.value().endX();
190 }
191 }
192 }
193 }
194 return rowIndicatorColumn;
195}
196
197static bool GetBarcodeMetadata(Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& leftRowIndicatorColumn, Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& rightRowIndicatorColumn, BarcodeMetadata& result)
198{
199 BarcodeMetadata leftBarcodeMetadata;
200 if (leftRowIndicatorColumn == nullptr || !leftRowIndicatorColumn.value().getBarcodeMetadata(leftBarcodeMetadata)) {
201 return rightRowIndicatorColumn != nullptr && rightRowIndicatorColumn.value().getBarcodeMetadata(result);
202 }
203
204 BarcodeMetadata rightBarcodeMetadata;
205 if (rightRowIndicatorColumn == nullptr || !rightRowIndicatorColumn.value().getBarcodeMetadata(rightBarcodeMetadata)) {
206 result = leftBarcodeMetadata;
207 return true;
208 }
209
210 if (leftBarcodeMetadata.columnCount() != rightBarcodeMetadata.columnCount() &&
211 leftBarcodeMetadata.errorCorrectionLevel() != rightBarcodeMetadata.errorCorrectionLevel() &&
212 leftBarcodeMetadata.rowCount() != rightBarcodeMetadata.rowCount()) {
213 return false;
214 }
215 result = leftBarcodeMetadata;
216 return true;
217}
218
219template <typename Iter>
220static auto GetMax(Iter start, Iter end) -> typename std::remove_reference<decltype(*start)>::type
221{
222 auto it = std::max_element(start, end);
223 return it != end ? *it : -1;
224}
225
226static bool AdjustBoundingBox(Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& rowIndicatorColumn, Nullable<BoundingBox>& result)
227{
228 if (rowIndicatorColumn == nullptr) {
229 result = nullptr;
230 return true;
231 }
232 std::vector<int> rowHeights;
233 if (!rowIndicatorColumn.value().getRowHeights(rowHeights)) {
234 result = nullptr;
235 return true;
236 }
237 int maxRowHeight = GetMax(rowHeights.begin(), rowHeights.end());
238 int missingStartRows = 0;
239 for (int rowHeight : rowHeights) {
240 missingStartRows += maxRowHeight - rowHeight;
241 if (rowHeight > 0) {
242 break;
243 }
244 }
245 auto& codewords = rowIndicatorColumn.value().allCodewords();
246 for (int row = 0; missingStartRows > 0 && codewords[row] == nullptr; row++) {
247 missingStartRows--;
248 }
249 int missingEndRows = 0;
250 for (int row = (int)rowHeights.size() - 1; row >= 0; row--) {
251 missingEndRows += maxRowHeight - rowHeights[row];
252 if (rowHeights[row] > 0) {
253 break;
254 }
255 }
256 for (int row = (int)codewords.size() - 1; missingEndRows > 0 && codewords[row] == nullptr; row--) {
257 missingEndRows--;
258 }
259 BoundingBox box;
260 if (BoundingBox::AddMissingRows(rowIndicatorColumn.value().boundingBox(), missingStartRows, missingEndRows, rowIndicatorColumn.value().isLeftRowIndicator(), box)) {
261 result = box;
262 return true;
263 }
264 return false;
265}
266
267static bool Merge(Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& leftRowIndicatorColumn, Nullable<DetectionResultColumn>& rightRowIndicatorColumn, DetectionResult& result)
268{
269 if (leftRowIndicatorColumn != nullptr || rightRowIndicatorColumn != nullptr) {
270 BarcodeMetadata barcodeMetadata;
271 if (GetBarcodeMetadata(leftRowIndicatorColumn, rightRowIndicatorColumn, barcodeMetadata)) {
272 Nullable<BoundingBox> leftBox, rightBox, mergedBox;
273 if (AdjustBoundingBox(leftRowIndicatorColumn, leftBox) && AdjustBoundingBox(rightRowIndicatorColumn, rightBox) && BoundingBox::Merge(leftBox, rightBox, mergedBox)) {
274 result.init(barcodeMetadata, mergedBox);
275 return true;
276 }
277 }
278 }
279 return false;
280}

282static bool IsValidBarcodeColumn(const DetectionResult& detectionResult, int barcodeColumn)
283{
284 return barcodeColumn >= 0 && barcodeColumn <= detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount() + 1;
285}
286
287static int GetStartColumn(const DetectionResult& detectionResult, int barcodeColumn, int imageRow, bool leftToRight)
288{
289 int offset = leftToRight ? 1 : -1;
290 Nullable<Codeword> codeword;
291 if (IsValidBarcodeColumn(detectionResult, barcodeColumn - offset)) {
292 codeword = detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn - offset).value().codeword(imageRow);
293 }
294 if (codeword != nullptr) {
295 return leftToRight ? codeword.value().endX() : codeword.value().startX();
296 }
297 codeword = detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn).value().codewordNearby(imageRow);
298 if (codeword != nullptr) {
299 return leftToRight ? codeword.value().startX() : codeword.value().endX();
300 }
301 if (IsValidBarcodeColumn(detectionResult, barcodeColumn - offset)) {
302 codeword = detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn - offset).value().codewordNearby(imageRow);
303 }
304 if (codeword != nullptr) {
305 return leftToRight ? codeword.value().endX() : codeword.value().startX();
306 }
307 int skippedColumns = 0;
308
309 while (IsValidBarcodeColumn(detectionResult, barcodeColumn - offset)) {
310 barcodeColumn -= offset;
311 for (auto& previousRowCodeword : detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn).value().allCodewords()) {
312 if (previousRowCodeword != nullptr) {
313 return (leftToRight ? previousRowCodeword.value().endX() : previousRowCodeword.value().startX()) +
314 offset *
315 skippedColumns *
316 (previousRowCodeword.value().endX() - previousRowCodeword.value().startX());
317 }
318 }
319 skippedColumns++;
320 }
321 return leftToRight ? detectionResult.getBoundingBox().value().minX() : detectionResult.getBoundingBox().value().maxX();
322}
323
324static std::vector<std::vector<BarcodeValue>> CreateBarcodeMatrix(DetectionResult& detectionResult)
325{
326 std::vector<std::vector<BarcodeValue>> barcodeMatrix(detectionResult.barcodeRowCount());
327 for (auto& row : barcodeMatrix) {
328 row.resize(detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount() + 2);
329 }
330
331 int column = 0;
332 for (auto& resultColumn : detectionResult.allColumns()) {
333 if (resultColumn != nullptr) {
334 for (auto& codeword : resultColumn.value().allCodewords()) {
335 if (codeword != nullptr) {
336 int rowNumber = codeword.value().rowNumber();
337 if (rowNumber >= 0) {
338 if (rowNumber >= (int)barcodeMatrix.size()) {
339 // We have more rows than the barcode metadata allows for, ignore them.
340 continue;
341 }
342 barcodeMatrix[rowNumber][column].setValue(codeword.value().value());
343 }
344 }
345 }
346 }
347 column++;
348 }
349 return barcodeMatrix;
350}
351
352static int GetNumberOfECCodeWords(int barcodeECLevel)
353{
354 return 2 << barcodeECLevel;
355}
356
357static bool AdjustCodewordCount(const DetectionResult& detectionResult, std::vector<std::vector<BarcodeValue>>& barcodeMatrix)
358{
359 auto numberOfCodewords = barcodeMatrix[0][1].value();
360 int calculatedNumberOfCodewords = detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount() * detectionResult.barcodeRowCount() - GetNumberOfECCodeWords(detectionResult.barcodeECLevel());
361 if (numberOfCodewords.empty()) {
362 if (calculatedNumberOfCodewords < 1 || calculatedNumberOfCodewords > CodewordDecoder::MAX_CODEWORDS_IN_BARCODE) {
363 return false;
364 }
365 barcodeMatrix[0][1].setValue(calculatedNumberOfCodewords);
366 }
367 else if (numberOfCodewords[0] != calculatedNumberOfCodewords) {
368 // The calculated one is more reliable as it is derived from the row indicator columns
369 barcodeMatrix[0][1].setValue(calculatedNumberOfCodewords);
370 }
371 return true;
372}
373// +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Error Correction
374
375static const ModulusGF& GetModulusGF()
376{
377 static const ModulusGF field(CodewordDecoder::NUMBER_OF_CODEWORDS, 3);
378 return field;
379}
380
381static bool RunEuclideanAlgorithm(ModulusPoly a, ModulusPoly b, int R, ModulusPoly& sigma, ModulusPoly& omega)
382{
383 const ModulusGF& field = GetModulusGF();
384
385 // Assume a's degree is >= b's
386 if (a.degree() < b.degree()) {
387 swap(a, b);
388 }
389
390 ModulusPoly rLast = a;
391 ModulusPoly r = b;
392 ModulusPoly tLast = field.zero();
393 ModulusPoly t = field.one();
394
395 // Run Euclidean algorithm until r's degree is less than R/2
396 while (r.degree() >= R / 2) {
397 ModulusPoly rLastLast = rLast;
398 ModulusPoly tLastLast = tLast;
399 rLast = r;
400 tLast = t;
401
402 // Divide rLastLast by rLast, with quotient in q and remainder in r
403 if (rLast.isZero()) {
404 // Oops, Euclidean algorithm already terminated?
405 return false;
406 }
407 r = rLastLast;
408 ModulusPoly q = field.zero();
409 int denominatorLeadingTerm = rLast.coefficient(rLast.degree());
410 int dltInverse = field.inverse(denominatorLeadingTerm);
411 while (r.degree() >= rLast.degree() && !r.isZero()) {
412 int degreeDiff = r.degree() - rLast.degree();
413 int scale = field.multiply(r.coefficient(r.degree()), dltInverse);
414 q = q.add(field.buildMonomial(degreeDiff, scale));
415 r = r.subtract(rLast.multiplyByMonomial(degreeDiff, scale));
416 }
417
418 t = q.multiply(tLast).subtract(tLastLast).negative();
419 }
420
421 int sigmaTildeAtZero = t.coefficient(0);
422 if (sigmaTildeAtZero == 0) {
423 return false;
424 }
425
426 int inverse = field.inverse(sigmaTildeAtZero);
427 sigma = t.multiply(inverse);
428 omega = r.multiply(inverse);
429 return true;
430}
431
432static bool FindErrorLocations(const ModulusPoly& errorLocator, std::vector<int>& result)
433{
434 const ModulusGF& field = GetModulusGF();
435 // This is a direct application of Chien's search
436 int numErrors = errorLocator.degree();
437 result.resize(numErrors);
438 int e = 0;
439 for (int i = 1; i < field.size() && e < numErrors; i++) {
440 if (errorLocator.evaluateAt(i) == 0) {
441 result[e] = field.inverse(i);
442 e++;
443 }
444 }
445 return e == numErrors;
446}
447
448static std::vector<int> FindErrorMagnitudes(const ModulusPoly& errorEvaluator, const ModulusPoly& errorLocator, const std::vector<int>& errorLocations)
449{
450 const ModulusGF& field = GetModulusGF();
451 int errorLocatorDegree = errorLocator.degree();
452 std::vector<int> formalDerivativeCoefficients(errorLocatorDegree);
453 for (int i = 1; i <= errorLocatorDegree; i++) {
454 formalDerivativeCoefficients[errorLocatorDegree - i] = field.multiply(i, errorLocator.coefficient(i));
455 }
456
457 ModulusPoly formalDerivative(field, formalDerivativeCoefficients);
458 // This is directly applying Forney's Formula
459 std::vector<int> result(errorLocations.size());
460 for (size_t i = 0; i < result.size(); i++) {
461 int xiInverse = field.inverse(errorLocations[i]);
462 int numerator = field.subtract(0, errorEvaluator.evaluateAt(xiInverse));
463 int denominator = field.inverse(formalDerivative.evaluateAt(xiInverse));
464 result[i] = field.multiply(numerator, denominator);
465 }
466 return result;
467}

469/**
470* @param received received codewords
471* @param numECCodewords number of those codewords used for EC
472* @param erasures location of erasures
473* @return number of errors
474* @throws ChecksumException if errors cannot be corrected, maybe because of too many errors
475*/
476ZXING_EXPORT_TEST_ONLY
477bool DecodeErrorCorrection(std::vector<int>& received, int numECCodewords, const std::vector<int>& erasures, int& nbErrors)
478{
479 const ModulusGF& field = GetModulusGF();
480 ModulusPoly poly(field, received);
481 std::vector<int> S(numECCodewords);
482 bool error = false;
483 for (int i = numECCodewords; i > 0; i--) {
484 int eval = poly.evaluateAt(field.exp(i));
485 S[numECCodewords - i] = eval;
486 if (eval != 0) {
487 error = true;
488 }
489 }
490
491 if (!error) {
492 nbErrors = 0;
493 return true;
494 }
495
496 ModulusPoly knownErrors = field.one();
497 for (int erasure : erasures) {
498 int b = field.exp(Size(received) - 1 - erasure);
499 // Add (1 - bx) term:
500 ModulusPoly term(field, { field.subtract(0, b), 1 });
501 knownErrors = knownErrors.multiply(term);
502 }
503
504 ModulusPoly syndrome(field, S);
505 //syndrome = syndrome.multiply(knownErrors);
506
507 ModulusPoly sigma, omega;
508 if (!RunEuclideanAlgorithm(field.buildMonomial(numECCodewords, 1), syndrome, numECCodewords, sigma, omega)) {
509 return false;
510 }
511
512 //sigma = sigma.multiply(knownErrors);
513
514 std::vector<int> errorLocations;
515 if (!FindErrorLocations(sigma, errorLocations)) {
516 return false;
517 }
518
519 std::vector<int> errorMagnitudes = FindErrorMagnitudes(omega, sigma, errorLocations);
520
521 int receivedSize = Size(received);
522 for (size_t i = 0; i < errorLocations.size(); i++) {
523 int position = receivedSize - 1 - field.log(errorLocations[i]);
524 if (position < 0) {
525 return false;
526 }
527 received[position] = field.subtract(received[position], errorMagnitudes[i]);
528 }
529 nbErrors = Size(errorLocations);
530 return true;
531}

533// --------------------------------------- Error Correction
534
535/**
536* <p>Given data and error-correction codewords received, possibly corrupted by errors, attempts to
537* correct the errors in-place.</p>
538*
539* @param codewords data and error correction codewords
540* @param erasures positions of any known erasures
541* @param numECCodewords number of error correction codewords that are available in codewords
542* @throws ChecksumException if error correction fails
543*/
544static bool CorrectErrors(std::vector<int>& codewords, const std::vector<int>& erasures, int numECCodewords, int& errorCount)
545{
546 if ((int)erasures.size() > numECCodewords / 2 + MAX_ERRORS ||
547 numECCodewords < 0 ||
548 numECCodewords > MAX_EC_CODEWORDS) {
549 // Too many errors or EC Codewords is corrupted
550 return false;
551 }
552 return DecodeErrorCorrection(codewords, numECCodewords, erasures, errorCount);
553}
554
555/**
556* Verify that all is OK with the codeword array.
557*/
558static bool VerifyCodewordCount(std::vector<int>& codewords, int numECCodewords)
559{
560 if (codewords.size() < 4) {
561 // Codeword array size should be at least 4 allowing for
562 // Count CW, At least one Data CW, Error Correction CW, Error Correction CW
563 return false;
564 }
565 // The first codeword, the Symbol Length Descriptor, shall always encode the total number of data
566 // codewords in the symbol, including the Symbol Length Descriptor itself, data codewords and pad
567 // codewords, but excluding the number of error correction codewords.
568 int numberOfCodewords = codewords[0];
569 if (numberOfCodewords > (int)codewords.size()) {
570 return false;
571 }
572 if (numberOfCodewords == 0) {
573 // Reset to the length of the array - 8 (Allow for at least level 3 Error Correction (8 Error Codewords)
574 if (numECCodewords < (int)codewords.size()) {
575 codewords[0] = (int)codewords.size() - numECCodewords;
576 }
577 else {
578 return false;
579 }
580 }
581 return true;
582}
583
584static DecoderResult DecodeCodewords(std::vector<int>& codewords, int ecLevel, const std::vector<int>& erasures)
585{
586 if (codewords.empty()) {
587 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
588 }
589
590 int numECCodewords = 1 << (ecLevel + 1);
591 int correctedErrorsCount = 0;
592 if (!CorrectErrors(codewords, erasures, numECCodewords, correctedErrorsCount))
593 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
594
595 if (!VerifyCodewordCount(codewords, numECCodewords))
596 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
597
598 // Decode the codewords
599 auto result = DecodedBitStreamParser::Decode(codewords, ecLevel);
600 if (result.isValid()) {
601 result.setErrorsCorrected(correctedErrorsCount);
602 result.setErasures(Size(erasures));
603 }
604 return result;
605}

608/**
609* This method deals with the fact, that the decoding process doesn't always yield a single most likely value. The
610* current error correction implementation doesn't deal with erasures very well, so it's better to provide a value
611* for these ambiguous codewords instead of treating it as an erasure. The problem is that we don't know which of
612* the ambiguous values to choose. We try decode using the first value, and if that fails, we use another of the
613* ambiguous values and try to decode again. This usually only happens on very hard to read and decode barcodes,
614* so decoding the normal barcodes is not affected by this.
615*
616* @param erasureArray contains the indexes of erasures
617* @param ambiguousIndexes array with the indexes that have more than one most likely value
618* @param ambiguousIndexValues two dimensional array that contains the ambiguous values. The first dimension must
619* be the same length as the ambiguousIndexes array
620*/
621static DecoderResult CreateDecoderResultFromAmbiguousValues(int ecLevel, std::vector<int>& codewords, const std::vector<int>& erasureArray, const std::vector<int>& ambiguousIndexes, const std::vector<std::vector<int>>& ambiguousIndexValues)
622{
623 std::vector<int> ambiguousIndexCount(ambiguousIndexes.size(), 0);
624
625 int tries = 100;
626 while (tries-- > 0) {
627 for (size_t i = 0; i < ambiguousIndexCount.size(); i++) {
628 codewords[ambiguousIndexes[i]] = ambiguousIndexValues[i][ambiguousIndexCount[i]];
629 }
630 auto result = DecodeCodewords(codewords, ecLevel, erasureArray);
631 if (result.errorCode() != DecodeStatus::ChecksumError) {
632 return result;
633 }
634
635 if (ambiguousIndexCount.empty()) {
636 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
637 }
638 for (size_t i = 0; i < ambiguousIndexCount.size(); i++) {
639 if (ambiguousIndexCount[i] < (int)ambiguousIndexValues[i].size() - 1) {
640 ambiguousIndexCount[i]++;
641 break;
642 }
643 else {
644 ambiguousIndexCount[i] = 0;
645 if (i == ambiguousIndexCount.size() - 1) {
646 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
647 }
648 }
649 }
650 }
651 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
652}
653
654
655static DecoderResult CreateDecoderResult(DetectionResult& detectionResult)
656{
657 auto barcodeMatrix = CreateBarcodeMatrix(detectionResult);
658 if (!AdjustCodewordCount(detectionResult, barcodeMatrix)) {
659 return DecodeStatus::NotFound;
660 }
661 std::vector<int> erasures;
662 std::vector<int> codewords(detectionResult.barcodeRowCount() * detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount(), 0);
663 std::vector<std::vector<int>> ambiguousIndexValues;
664 std::vector<int> ambiguousIndexesList;
665 for (int row = 0; row < detectionResult.barcodeRowCount(); row++) {
666 for (int column = 0; column < detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount(); column++) {
667 auto values = barcodeMatrix[row][column + 1].value();
668 int codewordIndex = row * detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount() + column;
669 if (values.empty()) {
670 erasures.push_back(codewordIndex);
671 }
672 else if (values.size() == 1) {
673 codewords[codewordIndex] = values[0];
674 }
675 else {
676 ambiguousIndexesList.push_back(codewordIndex);
677 ambiguousIndexValues.push_back(values);
678 }
679 }
680 }
681 return CreateDecoderResultFromAmbiguousValues(detectionResult.barcodeECLevel(), codewords, erasures, ambiguousIndexesList, ambiguousIndexValues);
682}
683
684
685// TODO don't pass in minCodewordWidth and maxCodewordWidth, pass in barcode columns for start and stop pattern
686// columns. That way width can be deducted from the pattern column.
687// This approach also allows to detect more details about the barcode, e.g. if a bar type (white or black) is wider
688// than it should be. This can happen if the scanner used a bad blackpoint.
689DecoderResult
690ScanningDecoder::Decode(const BitMatrix& image, const Nullable<ResultPoint>& imageTopLeft, const Nullable<ResultPoint>& imageBottomLeft,
691 const Nullable<ResultPoint>& imageTopRight, const Nullable<ResultPoint>& imageBottomRight,
692 int minCodewordWidth, int maxCodewordWidth)
693{
694 BoundingBox boundingBox;
695 if (!BoundingBox::Create(image.width(), image.height(), imageTopLeft, imageBottomLeft, imageTopRight, imageBottomRight, boundingBox)) {
696 return DecodeStatus::NotFound;
697 }
698
699 Nullable<DetectionResultColumn> leftRowIndicatorColumn, rightRowIndicatorColumn;
700 DetectionResult detectionResult;
701 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
702 if (imageTopLeft != nullptr) {
703 leftRowIndicatorColumn = GetRowIndicatorColumn(image, boundingBox, imageTopLeft, true, minCodewordWidth, maxCodewordWidth);
704 }
705 if (imageTopRight != nullptr) {
706 rightRowIndicatorColumn = GetRowIndicatorColumn(image, boundingBox, imageTopRight, false, minCodewordWidth, maxCodewordWidth);
707 }
708 if (!Merge(leftRowIndicatorColumn, rightRowIndicatorColumn, detectionResult)) {
709 return DecodeStatus::NotFound;
710 }
711 if (i == 0 && detectionResult.getBoundingBox() != nullptr && (detectionResult.getBoundingBox().value().minY() < boundingBox.minY() || detectionResult.getBoundingBox().value().maxY() > boundingBox.maxY())) {
712 boundingBox = detectionResult.getBoundingBox();
713 }
714 else {
715 detectionResult.setBoundingBox(boundingBox);
716 break;
717 }
718 }
719
720 int maxBarcodeColumn = detectionResult.barcodeColumnCount() + 1;
721 detectionResult.setColumn(0, leftRowIndicatorColumn);
722 detectionResult.setColumn(maxBarcodeColumn, rightRowIndicatorColumn);
723
724 bool leftToRight = leftRowIndicatorColumn != nullptr;
725 for (int barcodeColumnCount = 1; barcodeColumnCount <= maxBarcodeColumn; barcodeColumnCount++) {
726 int barcodeColumn = leftToRight ? barcodeColumnCount : maxBarcodeColumn - barcodeColumnCount;
727 if (detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn) != nullptr) {
728 // This will be the case for the opposite row indicator column, which doesn't need to be decoded again.
729 continue;
730 }
731 DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator rowIndicator = barcodeColumn == 0 ? DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator::Left : (barcodeColumn == maxBarcodeColumn ? DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator::Right : DetectionResultColumn::RowIndicator::None);
732 detectionResult.setColumn(barcodeColumn, DetectionResultColumn(boundingBox, rowIndicator));
733 int startColumn = -1;
734 int previousStartColumn = startColumn;
735 // TODO start at a row for which we know the start position, then detect upwards and downwards from there.
736 for (int imageRow = boundingBox.minY(); imageRow <= boundingBox.maxY(); imageRow++) {
737 startColumn = GetStartColumn(detectionResult, barcodeColumn, imageRow, leftToRight);
738 if (startColumn < 0 || startColumn > boundingBox.maxX()) {
739 if (previousStartColumn == -1) {
740 continue;
741 }
742 startColumn = previousStartColumn;
743 }
744 Nullable<Codeword> codeword = DetectCodeword(image, boundingBox.minX(), boundingBox.maxX(), leftToRight, startColumn, imageRow, minCodewordWidth, maxCodewordWidth);
745 if (codeword != nullptr) {
746 detectionResult.column(barcodeColumn).value().setCodeword(imageRow, codeword);
747 previousStartColumn = startColumn;
748 minCodewordWidth = std::min(minCodewordWidth, codeword.value().width());
749 maxCodewordWidth = std::max(maxCodewordWidth, codeword.value().width());
750 }
751 }
752 }
753 return CreateDecoderResult(detectionResult);
754}
